To concatenate sheets from two different workbooks (Google Sheets), you can modify the script accordingly. Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
function concatenateSheetsFromDifferentWorkbooks() {
  // Open the first workbook
  var workbook1 = SpreadsheetApp.openById("WORKBOOK1_ID");
  var sheet1 = workbook1.getSheetByName("Sheet1");
  var data1 = sheet1.getDataRange().getValues();

  // Open the second workbook
  var workbook2 = SpreadsheetApp.openById("WORKBOOK2_ID");
  var sheet2 = workbook2.getSheetByName("Sheet2");
  var data2 = sheet2.getDataRange().getValues();

  // Combine data from both sheets
  var combinedData = data1.concat(data2);

  // Create a new sheet to store the combined data
  var newWorkbook = SpreadsheetApp.create("Combined Workbook");
  var newSheet = newWorkbook.getActiveSheet();

  // Set the values of the new sheet to the combined data
  newSheet.getRange(1, 1, combinedData.length, combinedData[0].length).setValues(combinedData);
}
```

In this script:

1. Replace "WORKBOOK1_ID" and "WORKBOOK2_ID" with the IDs of the two different workbooks you want to concatenate.
2. Open each workbook using `SpreadsheetApp.openById()` and obtain the sheets you want to concatenate data from.
3. Retrieve the data from each sheet using `getDataRange().getValues()`.
4. Combine the data from both sheets.
5. Create a new workbook using `SpreadsheetApp.create()`.
6. Get the active sheet from the new workbook and set its values to the combined data using `setValues()`.

After you've made these changes, you can follow the same deployment steps mentioned earlier to deploy the script as a web app and run it to concatenate the sheets from the two different workbooks.

